# Linux Fundamentals

## Navigation
pwd -> shows current directory
ls -> lists files
cd -> change directory

## File Handling
nano -> create/edit files
cat -> view file contents

## Permissions
r = read
w = write
x = execute

chmod +x file -> makes file executable

## Searching
grep "text" file -> finds text

## Processes
ps -> shows processes
top -> live system monitor

## What I Learned
- How to navigate Linux using terminal
- How to create and edit files
- How file permissions work
- How to search and monitor processes
